## 📖 Overview

The **7400 IC** is a member of the **TTL (Transistor-Transistor Logic)** family and contains **four independent 2-input NAND gates** in a single package.

It is one of the most widely used integrated circuits in digital electronics and serves as a fundamental building block for logic circuit design.

