## 🌍 Universal Logic Gate

The NAND gate is called a **Universal Gate** because every basic logic gate can be implemented using only NAND gates.

✅ NOT Gate

✅ AND Gate

✅ OR Gate

✅ NOR Gate

✅ XOR Gate

✅ XNOR Gate

---

## 🔄 Implementing Other Gates

### NOT Gate

```text
A ----+
      |
      +---- NAND ---- Y
      |
A ----+
```

Result:

```text
Y = ¬A
```

### AND Gate

```text
Y = (A NAND B) NAND (A NAND B)
```

### OR Gate

Using De Morgan's Theorem:

```text
Y = (A NAND A) NAND (B NAND B)
```

